  "prompt": "Operator: softmax along last axis (out[i, :] = softmax(x[i, :]) so each row sums to 1); use asc2.softmax on a block of full rows. Input shapes: [32, 4096] ONLY (full-row regime; do not test other shapes \u2014 split_row is a separate cell, deferred to Phase 5/8). Output shape: same_as_input. Dtype: float16. Layout: contiguous. Axis: -1 (last axis). Tiling: row_per_core via block-of-rows distribution: block_size = ceildiv(num_rows, CORE_NUM), start_row = block_idx * block_size; each row fits in UB. Tail: aligned_only (split_row and long_rows_exceeding_UB are unsupported). Accumulator: float32 (softmax exp accumulates in fp32 internally). Tolerance: atol=5e-2, rtol=5e-2 against numpy reference computed as shifted = x - x.max(axis=1, keepdims=True); e = np.exp(shifted); expected = e / e.sum(axis=1, keepdims=True); verify in float32: np.testing.assert_allclose(out.astype(np.float32), expected.astype(np.float32), atol=5e-2, rtol=5e-2). Platform: Ascend950PR_9599. Build/run: python3.10 kernel.py -r Model -v Ascend950PR_9599. Evidence: kernel.py (skills-on adds design.md + verification.md).",
